@dahomiee The only decent Tyler Perry movie is his recent World War II drama, The Six Triple Eight. It’s based on a true story about 855 black women soldiers who served overseas during the war. There were many good reviews from viewers and it’s his most watched Netflix movie out of all of his other ones. Also, it’s Oscar nominated.

Another decent movie from him is his other period piece titled, A Jazzman’s Blues.

Both of those movies are worth a watch from Perry.
